Kubernetes Objects
------------------
Kubernetes object is an record of intent, through which we ask/tell kubernetes control-plane what we wanted to perform/create on cluster. Upon creating the object kubernetes cluster will tries to bring system/cluster to the desired state based on the object definition. All the kubernetes objects are persisted permanently aspart of the etcd.
  
There are different types of kubernetes objects are there
1. pod
2. replicaset
3. deploymentset
4. daemonset
5. job
6. service
7. ingress
8. loadbalancer
etc..
